:::Herald looks at his work table. It was covered in Chemicals rocks books 
and tools. For the past three days he and DataStreak had been working on the 
human art of alchemy, wile Tranquility and Defection had been studying Human 
Religion. Herald had finally made what he had wanted to make, The 
Philosophers Mercury, it was a stone that could change levels of gravity in a 
radius of fifty feet. He looked at his creation and was happy:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
:::Tranquility looked at he notes. Fifty-three pages on Angels. She had UN 
locked the secret she had been looking for. Angels were either dead soles or 
sparks, or, if they were living Angels, were related to one of the first 
children of the Matrix, 'God'. She had to keep looking, there was something 
about Cherubs that just nagged her!:::
